\bar X
\sigma^2/n
Var(nX) = n^2Var(X)
\sigma^2
 Var(\bar X) = E[\bar X^2] - E[\bar X]^2                = E[\bar X^2] - \mu^2                = E[(1/n\sum X_i)^2] - \mu^2                = 1/n^2 E[(\sum X_i)^2] - \mu^2                = 1/n^2 (n^2E[X^2]) - \mu^2               = Var(X) 
E \left[ \left(\sum X_i \right)^2 \right]
Y=\sum X_i.
E[Y]= n \mu.
\mathrm{Var} (Y)= n \sigma^2.
E[Y^2]=n \sigma^2 + n^2 \mu^2.
\mathrm{Var} (\bar X ) = {1 \over n^2} \left[ n \sigma^2 + n^2 \mu^2 \right] - \mu^2 = {\sigma^2 \over n}
